      <div class="msgContentFrame">So...because of the limited number of action points we get, combined with the wide range of DoT's, debuffs, and nukes that THM gets, I'm having a tough time finding room for Tect, Shell, and some other CON spells I like on my action bar.  Is it possible to create some complex macros that essentially equip a new action to our bar, casts a buff, then switches back out to our regular actions?  (See example below) <br /> <br />/eaction 3 &quot;Protect&quot; <br />/eaction 4 &quot;Shell&quot; <br />/aoe on <br />/ac Protect &lt;me&gt; <br />/wait 5 <br />/ac Shell &lt;me&gt; <br />/wait 5 <br />/aoe off <br />/eaction 3 &quot;Gravity&quot; <br />/eaction 4 &quot;Slow&quot; <br /> <br />Would something like that work?  Macro space permitting of course. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 27th 2010  4:29pm by DonFlamenco </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>MUTED</div></div>
